    "body": "This PR executes the shared_experts part of the FusedMoE on a separate GPU stream, so that the execution is parallelized with the \"selected_experts\" part. This is possible since the outputs of both are independent and are later combined. Thanks @wenscarl for pointing this out.\n\nFor DeepSeekR1 FP8 with Flashinfer latency kernels (trtllm-gen) on 8xB200s batch size 32, the TPOT improves from 23.35ms to 22.09ms (with latest FlashInfer codebase), so about ~5.7% e2e improvement.\n\n\n",
    "created_at": "2025-10-08T19:46:58Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-11-07T20:22:59Z",
    "closed_at": "2025-10-21T21:38:29Z",
